<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9514> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9514" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/10> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "ref. 154" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7322> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7322" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Monetalis. In MRR 2.436, and Index, 549, refer also to Crawford, RRC 1.222, no. 154, 189-180 B.C., a dating which makes it possible to identify the monetalis with the legatus of 170- 169 (RE no. 1; see MRR 1.422, in Illyricum). Could he have taken from his Macedonian service the cognomen Antipater, which was held in the next generation by the historian? (Sumner, Orators 57, with stemma).\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2690> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2690" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Held command in Illyria, and made an unsuccessful attempt during the winter 170-169 to recapture Uscana from a Macedonian garrison (Liv. 43.21.1-3; cf. above, on Claudius Centho)." .
